posts.raw_content:
I do some political consulting, mainly for state and local candidates and issues. Data research, voter registration, and overall campaign strategies.  In the last three weeks, I have been contacted by several Democrat pacs for creating and supporting campaign strategies. The Democrats are putting in a ton of money into this next election.  Two things are clear.  First, Democrats are completely  out of touch with reality.  Secondly, while the Democrats are out of touch, Republicans still need to get their ass in gear. I generally entertain the offers mainly out of curiosity and ask what their overall goal is. You will not believe the crazy responses I get. One pac just told me yesterday:

1. "We need a strategy to defeat Trump in 2028."

I hear this, or a variation of it often. I usually ask why they are not discussing beating JD Vance, Marco Rubio, or Ron DeSantis. They immediately say because Trump is going to run again and declare martial law to stay in office.  They reference being able to buy his 2028 hat in the capitol gift shop.  They never listen when I discuss that running on a strategy of solely "beating Trump" has never worked. It didn't work for Hillary, it didn't work for Biden, it didn't work for Kamala, it didn't work in state or local elections, it didn't work for the media. When I ask if they think Trump is just trolling them or the media with a 2028 run they look at me dumbfounded and say no. "He's serious about the presidency in 2028!". These people are completely nuts. While I would love a Trump 2028 presidency, let's be honest, it's not going to happen. 

2. "Antifa is an idea not an organization."

Marching orders are in.  Since they can't control them, they will just lie and pretend that antifa doesn't really exist. Despite leftwing violence, they admit they can't control their own lunatics so they are now just calling it an idea despite the paper trail of money from Democrat pacs, supporters, and politicians to antifa and like minded organizations. 

3. "We need to remind people of the darkest day in US history: The capitol insurrection." 

They think this is a winning strategy.  Despite the fact that evidence has over 250 FBI agent instigators. When I bring up polling that Americans do not change their political beliefs based on the "insurrection", they say I'm wrong and they need to exploit it. There is nothing left to exploit.  They have leveraged it as far as it can go, and now average Americans don't believe there was an "insurrection ".  

4. "Dream ticket is Newsome and AOC. 

They honestly think this is a winning ticket.  They reference polls that people across the country love the fact that Newsome is "going after Trump ". I remind them that Trump is probably not running and that it's not an efficient strategy.  They don't care. 

Some things are very clear preparing for this election.  
Democrats are putting a ton of money into this one. To even reach out to someone like me for consultation is crazy. They are not even vetting anyone anymore.  Just writing checks.  

As far as registration data.  They are attempting to steal swing states. We didn't see this as much in the last election.  But even this early they are registering a ton of people. Trump needs to enact stricter voter laws and mandate a new census immediately.  On this note if you want to help with this one, download your states voter registration rolls. This usually costs 20-40 dollars but shows everyone registered in your state and affiliation. Look for abnormalities. Duplicate names, DOBs, but most importantly, organize by address. You may find hundreds of people registered at the same address, government buildings, or FedEx locations.  Cross connect to other states for the same name and date of birth. Check city and town populations to compare against registration.  You will find some cities that have over 100% voting rates. Which of course is impossible. Report any abnormalities to your secretary of state. Especially if your secretary of state is conservative. If you are in a Democrat state, submit it to the republican party for your state.  They have lawyers that will file to have them removed from the rolls so they can't vote. 

Another thing that is clear is how out of touch the Democrat party is. They are not even attempting to go after the housing market, wages, unions or anything else that has previously won elections for them. They just want to attack Trump.  There are no real strategies coming out of their party. 

This tells us one of two things. A. They don't care to win back votes because stealing them is easier. B. They are so out of touch that they have no idea that they have lost the common American. Most likely a combination of both. 

Anywho, I thought some of you might enjoy some insights to what the Democrat pacs are saying and thinking.
